## üîß PyPI Token Configuration

To avoid entering your PyPI token every time, use one of these methods:

### Option 1: `.pypirc` File (Recommended)

Create `~/.pypirc` (or `%USERPROFILE%\.pypirc` on Windows):

```ini
[pypi]
username = __token__
password = pypi-YourActualTokenHere

[testpypi]
username = __token__
password = pypi-YourTestPyPITokenHere
```

**Security Note**: Make sure `.pypirc` is in `.gitignore` and never commit it!

### Option 2: Environment Variables

Set in your shell profile (`.bashrc`, `.zshrc`, or Windows environment variables):

```bash
export TWINE_USERNAME=__token__
export TWINE_PASSWORD=pypi-YourActualTokenHere
```

### Option 3: Keyring (Most Secure)

```bash
py -m pip install keyring
py -m keyring set https://upload.pypi.org/legacy/ __token__
# Enter your token when prompted
```

Then use normally:
```bash
py -m twine upload dist/*
```

